message.content:
cs.HCI, cs.CYBER, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.HCI (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing a system that enables effective crowd teams through a user interface that allows workers to assemble familiar teams. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is also likely as the paper discusses the challenges of ensuring security and privacy in crowd work, especially when dealing with sensitive data. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper explores the dynamics of team formation and collaboration in crowd work. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as the paper utilizes a dynamic programming algorithm to optimize for highly familiar teammates when individual availability is unknown. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also relevant as the paper discusses the algorithmic approach used in the system design.
